七七.desc: An apprentice and herb gatherer at Bubu Pharmacy. An undead with a bone-white complexion, she seldom has much in the way of words or emotion.

丝柯克.desc: A visitor who once appeared in an Abyssal rift and the Primordial Sea, this solitary warrior mentored Tartaglia in the martial arts.

丽莎.desc: The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Akademiya to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.

久岐忍.desc: The capable and reliable Arataki Gang deputy leader. Please note: capable and reliable are not appellations for the "Arataki Gang," but for their deputy leader in specific.

九条裟罗.desc: A general of the Tenryou Commission. Bold, decisive, and skilled in battle.

云堇.desc: A renowned Liyue opera singer who is skilled in both playwriting and singing. Her style is one-of-a-kind, exquisite and delicate, much like the person herself.

五郎.desc: The great general of Watatsumi Island's forces. He is deeply trusted by his subordinates.

伊安珊.desc: Head coach of the fitness club at the Collective of Plenty, and a renowned Natlanese nutritionist.

伊法.desc: A vet from the Flower-Feather Clan who cherishes the life he leads alongside all manner of living things — people, animals, you name it.

伊涅芙.desc: A multifunctional robot containing integrated mechanical components from various nations. The Source Core in her chest has endured the passage of countless years.

优菈.desc: The Spindrift Knight, a scion of the old aristocracy, and the Captain of the Knights of Favonius Reconnaissance Company. The reason for which a descendant of the ancient nobles might join the Knights remains a great mystery in Mondstadt to this very day.

克洛琳德.desc: An undefeated Champion Duelist. Sword in hand, she defends justice in the Court of Fontaine.

八重神子.desc: Lady Guuji of the Grand Narukami Shrine. Also serves as the editor-in-chief of Yae Publishing House. Unimaginable intelligence and cunning are hidden under her beautiful appearance.

凝光.desc: The Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Her wealth is unsurpassed in all of Teyvat.

凯亚.desc: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.

刻晴.desc: The Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Keqing has much to say about Rex Lapis's unilateral approach to policymaking in Liyue — but in truth, gods admire skeptics such as her quite a lot.

北斗.desc: Captain of her crew, The Crux. She's quite an unbound and forthright woman.

千织.desc: The owner of Chioriya Boutique. A tailor renowned throughout Fontaine.

卡维.desc: A renowned architect from Sumeru who perhaps cares a bit too much about too many things. He is an aesthete troubled by reality.

卡齐娜.desc: A young warrior of the Nanatzcayan, given the Ancient Name of "Uthabiti." Kind-hearted and insatiably persistent, she grows stronger and more capable with each setback she faces.

可莉.desc: An explosives expert and a regular at the Knights of Favonius's confinement room. Also known as Fleeing Sunlight.

嘉明.desc: Guard of the Sword and Strongbox Secure Transport Agency, and the head of the "Mighty Mythical Beasts" Wushou troupe.

坎蒂丝.desc: A descendant of King Deshret with an amber left eye. The defender of Aaru Village.

埃洛伊.desc: Formerly an outcast, now a hunter of unparalleled skill. Ready to do the right thing at any time.

基尼奇.desc: A Huitztlan Saurian Hunter skilled at counting costs.

塔利雅.desc: Deacon of the Church of Favonius and the Anemo Archon's representative in the church.

夏沃蕾.desc: The captain of the Special Security and Surveillance Patrol, who wears justice as an ever-present seal upon her heart. Her musket shall only ever point at the guilty.

夏洛蒂.desc: Indefatigable reporter of The Steambird, constantly on the hunt for the "truth."

多莉.desc: An elusive merchant who has a fondness for glittering Mora.

夜兰.desc: A mysterious person who claims to work for the Ministry of Civil Affairs, but is a "non-entity" on the Ministry of Civil Affairs' list.

妮露.desc: The star of the Zubayr Theater. She is full of warmth and innocence, and her dances are lively and elegant.

娜维娅.desc: The current President of Spina di Rosula, who is lovely, dutiful, and a great boss.

安柏.desc: Always energetic and full of life, Amber's the best — albeit only — Outrider of the Knights of Favonius.

宵宫.desc: Owner of Naganohara Fireworks. Known as the "Queen of the Summer Festival," she excels in her craft of creating fireworks that symbolize people's hopes and dreams.

希格雯.desc: A Melusine and the Fortress of Meropide's head nurse. She cares equally for every convict locked in the undersea prison.

希诺宁.desc: A Name Engraver of the Nanatzcayan, she is especially skilled at finding a good balance between the heavy responsibilities of her job and living well.

恰斯卡.desc: The Peacemaker of the Tlalocan, the ender of all disputes.

托马.desc: The Kamisato Clan's housekeeper. A well-known "fixer" in Inazuma.

提纳里.desc: A young researcher well-versed in botany who currently serves as a Forest Watcher in Avidya Forest. He is a straight shooter with a warm heart — and a dab hand at guiding even the dullest of pupils.

旅行者.desc: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

早柚.desc: A pint-sized ninja attached to the Shuumatsuban, who always seems sleep-deprived.

林尼.desc: A famed Fontainian magician who possesses great stage presence as well as gift of the gab. Audiences are enthralled by his exquisite skills, and they hang on to his every clever word.

枫原万叶.desc: A wandering samurai from Inazuma who is currently with Liyue's Crux Fleet. A gentle and carefree soul whose heart hides a great many burdens from the past.

柯莱.desc: A trainee ranger active in Avidya Forest. Behind her enthusiastic words and actions hides a slightly introverted personality.

梦见月瑞希.desc: A shareholder of Aisa Bathhouse, a baku, and a clinical psychologist. Dedicated to the dispersal of nightmares, and to bringing people peace of mind.

欧洛伦.desc: A young man from the Masters of the Night-Wind who instead lives in the wild alongside all manner of life.

流浪者.desc: A wayfaring figure whose identity is a mystery. He dresses like a mountain ascetic, but he certainly does not act the part.

温迪.desc: One of the many bards of Mondstadt, who freely wanders the city's streets and alleys.

烟绯.desc: A well-known legal adviser active in Liyue Harbor. A brilliant young lady in whose veins runs the blood of an illuminated beast.

爱可菲.desc: The ex-head chef of Hotel Debord, renowned throughout Fontaine as the Patissiere Supreme and vanguard of precision gastronomy. Has incomparably strict standards when it comes to cooking.

爱诺.desc: A genius mechanic and inventor from Nod-Krai who loves interesting machines and sweet treats.

玛拉妮.desc: A well-known guide in Natlan who owns a watersports shop, and expert in all forms of wave-chasing.

玛薇卡.desc: The leader of Natlan who inherited the Ancient Name of "Kiongozi." She made a vow to illuminate the future of the nation of war with the Sacred Flame.

珊瑚宫心海.desc: The Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island. All of the island's affairs are at this young lady's fingertips.

珐露珊.desc: A researcher from "one hundred years ago." She enjoys self-identifying as everyone's senior, and has significant knowledge of ancient scripts and machines of all kinds.

班尼特.desc: A good-natured adventurer from Mondstadt who's unfortunately extremely unlucky.

琳妮特.desc: A magic assistant of few words, her emotions are as inscrutable as any cat's.

琴.desc: The righteous and rigorous Dandelion Knight, and Acting Grand Master of Mondstadt's Knights of Favonius.

瑶瑶.desc: Streetward Rambler's youngest disciple. A gentle and caring "little adult."

瓦雷莎.desc: A laid-back orchard manager and warrior of the Collective of Plenty. An aspiring hero who hungers for justice... and lots and lots of food!

甘雨.desc: The secretary at Yuehai Pavilion. The blood of the qilin, an illuminated beast, flows within her veins.

申鹤.desc: An adepti disciple with a most unusual air about her. Having spent much time cultivating in isolation in Liyue's mountains, she has become every bit as cool and distant as the adepti themselves.

白术.desc: The owner of Bubu Pharmacy, who is rarely seen without the white snake named Changsheng. His medicinal knowledge is encyclopedic, and his personal intrigues subtle.

砂糖.desc: An alchemist filled with curiosity about all things. She researches bio-alchemy.

神里绫人.desc: The young but highly accomplished head of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Cultured and polite, he is a man of many ways and means.

神里绫华.desc: Daughter of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Dignified and elegant, as well as wise and strong.

米卡.desc: A young knight born to an ordinary family. He serves as a Front-Line Surveyor in his Company. He is a low-key and cautious character.

纳西妲.desc: A caged bird secluded within the confines of the Sanctuary of Surasthana who can only see the world in her dreams.

绮良良.desc: A courier for Komaniya Express, a delivery company in Inazuma. A nekomata who loves her job and human society.

罗莎莉亚.desc: A sister of the church, though you wouldn't know it if it weren't for her attire. Known for her sharp, cold words and manner, she often works alone.

胡桃.desc: The 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. She took over the business at a rather young age.

艾尔海森.desc: The current scribe of the Sumeru Akademiya, a man endowed with extraordinary intelligence and talent. He lives free — free from the searching eyes of ordinary people, anyway.

艾梅莉埃.desc: A Fontainian perfumer, one who bottles secrets.

芙宁娜.desc: The absolute focus of the stage of judgment, until the final applause sounds.

芭芭拉.desc: Every citizen of Mondstadt adores Barbara. She learned the word "idol" from a magazine.

茜特菈莉.desc: The great shaman from the Masters of the Night-Wind, the universally-revered Granny Itztli.

荒泷一斗.desc: The first and greatest head of the Arataki Gang, famed throughout Inazuma City's Hanamizaka... Wait, what? You've never heard of them? Are you trying to be funny here?

莫娜.desc: A mysterious young astrologer who proclaims herself to be "Astrologist Mona Megistus," and who possesses abilities to match the title. Erudite, but prideful.

莱依拉.desc: A Rtawahist student who specializes in Theoretical Astrology. Heavily prone to somnambulism and locked in a grinding war with sleep deprivation, the problem of restful slumber is a most troubling one to her.

莱欧斯利.desc: Duke of the Fortress of Meropide, Lord Incognito of the murky depths.

菈乌玛.desc: A Maiden blessed by moonlight and the grove alike, hope born to the Frostmoon Scions.

菲林斯.desc: A Lightkeeper of Nod-Krai, guardian of a lighthouse and graveyard on a northern isle. An enigmatic gentleman, cultured and courtly.

菲米尼.desc: A reserved young man who is well-versed in diving. Beneath his distant, icy demeanor lies a pure heart bereft of all flaws.

菲谢尔.desc: A mysterious girl who calls herself "Prinzessin der Verurteilung" and travels with a night raven named Oz.

蓝砚.desc: A rattan weaver from Chenyu Vale. Clear-minded and well-tempered, she is as lively as a mountain spring.

行秋.desc: A young man carrying a longsword who is frequently seen at book booths. He has a chivalrous heart and yearns for justice and fairness for all.

诺艾尔.desc: A maid who faithfully serves the Knights of Favonius. She dreams of joining their ranks someday.

赛索斯.desc: The Temple of Silence's heir. Burdened with secrets, he comes from the sands.

赛诺.desc: The General Mahamatra in charge of supervising the researchers of the Akademiya. It is said that when he gets down to work, the General Mahamatra is even more efficient than the "Great Vayuvyastra" made by the Kshahrewar.

辛焱.desc: Liyue's sole rock 'n' roll musician. She rebels against ossified prejudices using her music and passionate singing.

达达利亚.desc: No. 11 of The Harbingers, also known as "Childe." His name is highly feared on the battlefield.

迪卢克.desc: The tycoon of a winery empire in Mondstadt, unmatched in every possible way.

迪奥娜.desc: A young lady who has inherited trace amounts of non-human blood. She is the incredibly popular bartender of the Cat's Tail tavern.

迪希雅.desc: A member of the Eremites, a mercenary organization that roams the sands of Sumeru. Valiant and powerful, she enjoys great fame amongst her fellow Eremites.

那维莱特.desc: The Chief Justice of Fontaine, known as the Iudex, is renowned for his unassailable impartiality.

重云.desc: A young exorcist from a family of exorcists. He does everything he can to suppress his abundance of yang energy.

钟离.desc: A mysterious expert contracted by the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. Extremely knowledgeable in all things.

闲云.desc: One of the Mighty and Illuminated Adepti of Jueyun, known as "Cloud Retainer." Expert in all kinds of mechanical contraptions, her heart now turns towards the affairs of the mortal world, through which she walks under the name "Xianyun."

阿蕾奇诺.desc: "The Knave," Fourth of the Fatui Harbingers. A poised, ruthless diplomat. To the children in the House of the Hearth, she is their feared yet dependable "Father."

阿贝多.desc: A genius known as the Kreideprinz, he is the Chief Alchemist and Captain of the Investigation Team of the Knights of Favonius.

雷泽.desc: A boy who lives among the wolves in Wolvendom of Mondstadt, away from human civilization. As agile as lightning.

雷电将军.desc: Her Excellency, the Almighty Narukami Ogosho, who promised the people of Inazuma an unchanging Eternity.

香菱.desc: A renowned chef from Liyue. She's extremely passionate about cooking and excels at making her signature hot and spicy dishes.

魈.desc: A yaksha adeptus who defends Liyue. Also heralded as the "Conqueror of Demons" and "Vigilant Yaksha."

鹿野院平藏.desc: A young prodigy detective from the Tenryou Commission. His senses are sharp and his thoughts are clear.
